 ğŸŸ¥ PROBLEMS WITH SCRUM (Technical + Simple example)

Scrum is good for planned development
but not good for unplanned or urgent work

---

 ğŸ”´ Problem 1: Sprint cannot change (technical)

 ğŸ“˜ Technical explanation

In Scrum:

 Sprint duration fixed (2 weeks)
 Sprint backlog locked
 New tasks cannot be added

Reason:
Team focus should not change during sprint.

But real IT world:

 Production bugs come
 Client urgent change
 Server down

You cannot wait till next sprint.

---

 ğŸ‘©â€â¤ï¸â€ğŸ‘¨ Husband-wife example

Wife gives list:

 Buy vegetables
 Clean house
 Pay bill

Husband plans full day.

Suddenly guests coming.

Wife:

> Go bring sweets also

Husband:

> Already planned tasks ğŸ˜‘

But real life:
He must go immediately.

Scrum fails here.

---

 ğŸ¢ Real IT example

Sprint started Monday.

Wednesday:
Production payment failure.

Client losing money.

Can team say:

> We will fix next sprint?

No.

So Scrum rigid structure becomes problem.

---

 ğŸ”´ Problem 2: Too many meetings

 ğŸ“˜ Technical explanation

Scrum has many ceremonies:

 Sprint planning
 Daily standup
 Sprint review
 Retrospective

If team small â†’ fine
If project heavy â†’ time-consuming

Sometimes more meeting, less work.

---

 ğŸ‘©â€â¤ï¸â€ğŸ‘¨ Example

