 ğŸŸ© So companies introduced KANBAN

 ğŸŸ© What is Kanban? (technical)

Kanban = Continuous workflow system.

No sprint.
No fixed commitment.
Work taken as it comes.

Board:

```
To Do â†’ In Progress â†’ Done
```

Work flows continuously.

---

 ğŸ“˜ Technical features of Kanban

1. No sprint
2. Continuous delivery
3. Work in progress (WIP) limit
4. Visual board tracking
5. Flexible priorities

---

 ğŸ‘©â€â¤ï¸â€ğŸ‘¨ Example

Daily home tasks board:

To do:

 Buy milk
 Wash clothes

In progress:

 Cooking

Done:

 Cleaning

Pick task anytime.
Finish anytime.

No 2-week planning.

---

 ğŸ¢ Real IT example

Production support team:
Bug comes â†’ fix
Next bug â†’ fix
Urgent issue â†’ handle

No sprint wait.

---

 ğŸŸ¥ EXTREME PROGRAMMING (XP)

 ğŸ“˜ Technical meaning

XP focuses on:
ğŸ‘‰ High-quality coding
ğŸ‘‰ Continuous testing
ğŸ‘‰ Frequent releases
ğŸ‘‰ Developer collaboration

Used in critical systems.

---

 ğŸ‘©â€â¤ï¸â€ğŸ‘¨ Example

